Citation.sTitle: A systematic study on physicochemical and transport properties of imidazolium-based ionic liquids with gamma-butyrolactone
Citation.sAbstract: Densities, viscosities and electrical conductivities were determined and discussed for gamma-butyrolactone (GBL) with 1,3-dimethylimidazolium bis(trifluoromethylsulfonyl)imide ionic liquid ([mmim][NTf2]) binary mixtures as a function of temperature at atmospheric pressure over the whole composition range. From the experimental density data the related excess molar volumes were calculated and fitted using Redlich Kister s polynomial equation. The thermal expansion coefficients were also calculated from the acquired experimental density values. Electrical conductivity data were correlated using Casteel Amis and Arrhenius equations. The influence of viscosity on electrical conductivity was discussed within the scope of Walden rule. Volumetric and transport properties of GBL binary mixtures with selected ionic liquid are compared with available literature data for the corresponding 1-methyl-3-alkylsupstituted imidazolium based ILs.
